An Act establishing a holiday known as "John F. Kennedy Day" to promote civic engagement
and voter participation in the Commonwealth.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 7 of chapter 4 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2018
2 Official Edition, is hereby amended by inserting after the word “October,”, in line 100, the
3 following words:- John F. Kennedy Day.
4 SECTION 2. Section 15L of chapter 6 of the General Laws, as so appearing, is hereby
5 amended by inserting after the word “November”, in line 2, the following words:- in all odd-
6 numbered years and the first Tuesday after the first Monday in November in all even-numbered
7 years.
8 SECTION 3. Said chapter 6 is hereby further amended by adding the following section:-
1 of 2

9 Section 220. There shall be a commission on the celebration of John F. Kennedy Day.
10 The commission shall consist of: 2 persons to be appointed by the governor; 2 persons to be
11 appointed by the state secretary, 1 of whom shall be designated to serve as chair; 1 person to be
12 appointed by the speaker of the house of representatives; 1 person to be appointed by the
13 minority leader of the house of representatives; 1 person to be appointed by the president of the
14 senate; 1 person to be appointed by the minority leader of the senate; 1 person to be appointed by
15 the executive director of the John F. Kennedy Library Foundation; 1 person to be appointed by
16 the president of the John F. Kennedy Hyannis Museum Foundation, Inc.; and 1 person to be
17 appointed by the president of the Edward M. Kennedy Institute for the United States Senate.
18 The commission shall recommend activities that promote civic engagement and voter
19 participation including, but not limited to: (i) establishing a Kindergarten to grade 12, inclusive,
20 education curriculum; (ii) hosting special events; (iii) marketing, which shall include the
21 publication and distribution of materials and online content; (iv) voter engagement activities; (v)
22 voter registration drives; and (vi) voter access. The commission shall meet not less than
23 semiannually. The commission shall issue an annual report to the clerks of the senate and house
24 of representatives not later than December 31.
